HEADWORD: antitrust
<hw>antitrust</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>opposed to trusts,
monopolies, or other large combinations of business or capital which
threaten fair competition; designed to protect trade and commerce from
unfair business practices; -- of laws and regulations.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> antimonopoly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>antitussive</ent>⟦br⟧
